Rick Ross performs onstage at the BET Hip Hop Awards 2019 at Cobb Energy Center on October 5, 2019 in Atlanta, Georgia. JOHANNESBURG - American rapper Rick Ross is coming to South Africa to headline music festival Block Party in December. The Gold Roses hitmaker is set to perform in Durban and East London. WATCH: Kwesta shares township experience with Rick Ross "Block hop starts from Durban, Saturday, 21 December, Kings Park Stadium outer fields to East London, Sunday, 22 December, Buffalo Park Stadium. Featuring some of SAs biggest names in Hip Hop, House AmaPiano and Gqom as well as hot up and coming stars," said the organisers in a statement. Tickets for the festival are available here and start from R345.